.TH "OPENPASS" "1" "Apr 2026" "OpenPass" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
openpass-edit - Edit an existing password entry


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBopenpass edit  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens an existing password entry in your default editor for modification.

.PP
The entry is opened in JSON format. Save and exit the editor to update the entry.
If the entry does not exist, an error is returned.

.PP
The editor is determined by the --editor flag or EDITOR environment variable (defaults to vi).

.EX
Examples:
.EE

.PP
openpass edit github
  openpass edit work/aws
  openpass edit personal/bank --editor nano
  EDITOR=nano openpass edit personal/bank


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--editor\fP=""
	Editor to use (overrides EDITOR env var)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for edit


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBopenpass(1)\fP
